ration and lifetime restrictions for human users","description":"The control system shall provide the capability to prevent any given human user account from reusing a password for a configurable number of generations. In addition, the control system shall provide the capability to enforce password minimum and maximum lifetime restrictions for human users. These capabilities shall conform with commonly accepted security industry practices.","note":"It is a commonly accepted good practice that the control system provides the capability to prompt the user to change his password upon a configurable time prior to expiration."},{"id":"SR 1.7 RE 2","name":"Password lifetime restrictions for all users","description":"The control system shall provide the capability to enforce password minimum and maximum lifetime restrictions for all users."}],"security_levels":["SL-C (IAC, control system) 1: SR 1.7","SL-C (IAC, control system) 2: SR 1.7","SL-C (IAC, control system) 3: SR 1.7 (1)","SL-C (IAC, control system) 4: SR 1.7 (1) (2)"]} 
